A vibrant, cartoonish dragon bursts forward from a distressed urban wall, rendered in exaggerated, high-detail illustration. The creature’s body is compact and muscular, covered in textured red scales with pale, segmented underbelly plates stretching from jaw to torso. Its enormous mouth dominates the composition, opened wide in a dramatic roar or gleeful shout. Large, rounded teeth line the upper and lower jaws, and a long pink tongue curls toward the viewer, enhancing the sense of depth.
The dragon’s eyes are wide and animated, with pale blue irises and expressive, sharply angled brows that give it a mischievous, almost comedic intensity. Small horn-like protrusions rise from its head, and short, angular spikes trace along its back and tail. Both clawed hands reach outward as if lunging beyond the wall’s surface, adding a dynamic, three-dimensional illusion.
Behind and beneath the creature, a partially exposed brick wall shows torn posters, scattered paper fragments, and flecks of paint, suggesting layers of street art and urban decay. The background is muted gray, allowing the dragon’s saturated reds and warm tones to stand out boldly.
The overall atmosphere blends street graffiti culture with animated fantasy, creating a playful yet ferocious presence that feels as though it has ripped itself free from the masonry.

A warmly lit interior scene frames a woman standing in three-quarter profile within a softly shadowed bedroom. She turns her head toward the viewer with a subtle, knowing smile. Her auburn hair is styled in loose, voluminous waves, gathered back while gentle curls frame her face. The light from a nearby bedside lamp casts a golden glow across her skin, highlighting faint freckles and the delicate contours of her cheekbones and collarbones.

She wears a pale blush lace lingerie set with fine floral detailing and thin straps, layered beneath a sheer, matching robe that drapes loosely from her shoulders. The translucent fabric catches the lamplight, creating soft gradients of peach and amber along its folds. The textures of lace and silk are rendered with tactile precision, emphasizing their intricate patterns without overpowering the scene.

In the background, a small wooden dresser and framed wall art are softly blurred, while a glowing table lamp with a cream shade creates a pool of warm light that anchors the composition. To the right, a lace curtain hangs near a window, its delicate trim illuminated at the edge.

The atmosphere feels intimate yet composed, balancing vintage glamour with gentle modern clarity. The interplay of shadow and warm light turns the quiet room into a stage of understated elegance.

David Ingram ja Jonathan Tallant uusivat äsken SEP-entryään presentismistä, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/presentism/. Sitä lukiessa huomaan välillä hymyileväni. Selitys löytynee kirjoituksen erityisen analyyttisesta ja lukijaa palvelevasta tyylistä, joka näyttää harvinaistuvan tuossakin ensyklopediassa.

Toinen kiintoisa päivitys, Christopher Molen Attention https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/attention/, edustaa pikemmin filosofian naturalisoinnin mukanaan tuomaa, sinänsä ansiokasta empiiris-tieteellisen ajantasan tavoittelua. Se ei samalla tavoin kutittele aikanaan logiikan kautta matematiikka-vammaansa kätellyttä eläkeläistä. Hyytyi myös kenties kuranteimman teeman, huomiotalouden kynnykselle, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attention_economy

Laadukkaiden filosofis-tieteellisten tekstien verkkainen lukeminen on minulle vähän kuin vuolemista (whittling, carving), ja korvannee kohdallani ulkomaanmatkat, viihteen ja fantasiakirjallisuuden.
